{
  "text": "Silica. MCM-48 silica was prepared according to the procedure described in bibliography [CITATION_1] . The resultant silicate mixture was stirred for 1 h at room temperature and the samples were then collected by filtration and transferred to a Teflon lined steel vessel. The sample was then heated at 100 \u2218 C for 4 days. After the mixture was cooled, the precipitated product was washed with DI water and calcinated at 500 \u2218 C for 8 h. The MCM-48 was characterized by XRD and TEM analyses.",
